drh added on 2019-07-17 13:36:40:
When a CHECK constraint contains a CASE or BETWEEN operator with a left-hand
side that has a COLLATE operator, incorrect byte code is generated resulting
in an assertion fault.  Examples:
CREATE TABLE t1(a CHECK(1 COLLATE BINARY BETWEEN 1 AND 1));
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES('abc');
CREATE TABLE t1(a CHECK(CASE 'abc' COLLATE nocase WHEN a THEN 1 END));
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES('abc');
This problem appears to have arisen from check-in [54110870487f7801]
(2019-06-16) which was a fix for ticket [e1e07ef2028c3c22].
drh added on 2019-07-17 14:27:10:
The BETWEEN example above requires two inserts before it fails:
CREATE TABLE t1(a CHECK(1 COLLATE BINARY BETWEEN 1 AND 1));
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES('abc');
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES('abc');
drh added on 2019-07-17 14:28:46:
Actually, both examples require two INSERT statements.
